NNAAMMEE
       strlen - calculate the length of a string

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       ##iinncclluuddee <<ssttrriinngg..hh>>

       ssiizzee__tt ssttrrlleenn((ccoonnsstt cchhaarr **_s));;

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       The ssttrrlleenn() function calculates the length of the string pointed to by _s, excluding the terminating null byte ('\0').

RREETTUURRNN VVAALLUUEE
       The ssttrrlleenn() function returns the number of bytes in the string pointed to by _s.

AATTTTRRIIBBUUTTEESS
       For an explanation of the terms used in this section, see aattttrriibbuutteess(7).

       ┌──────────┬───────────────┬─────────┐
       │IInntteerrffaaccee │ AAttttrriibbuuttee     │ VVaalluuee   │
       ├──────────┼───────────────┼─────────┤
       │ssttrrlleenn()  │ Thread safety │ MT-Safe │
       └──────────┴───────────────┴─────────┘
CCOONNFFOORRMMIINNGG TTOO
       POSIX.1-2001, POSIX.1-2008, C89, C99, C11, SVr4, 4.3BSD.

SSEEEE AALLSSOO
       ssttrriinngg(3), ssttrrnnlleenn(3), wwccsslleenn(3), wwccssnnlleenn(3)

